tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine in serum and blood, proteinuria), hypoglycemia, and markedly low HbA1c. Urinalysis reveals protein, ketones, bilirubin, and abnormal appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or acute kidney injury with metabolic derangements. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Immediate clinical evaluation and nephrology referral are recommended.
